  <tr>
    <td bgcolor='0e024d' class='spti2'>THE DISCIPLINE OF FORTITUDE</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Class:</b>&nbsp;Warrior</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Level obtained:</b>&nbsp;59</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Duration:</b>&nbsp;8 seconds.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay:</b>&nbsp;60 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b>Re-Use Delay at Level 60:</b>&nbsp;59 minutes.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class='db'><b><u>Discipline Description:</u></b><P>When using this discipline the warrior cannot be hit in melee combat. This does not alter in anyway the ability for the warrior to have damage inflicted on them by magical means.  This discipline lasts for 8 seconds and has a base reuse time of 60 minutes.  The reuse time for this discipline will decrease as the warrior gains additional levels.</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>  <table border='0' width='100%' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='5'>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 bgcolor='#000066' class='spti2'>DISCIPLINE COMMENTS</td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>FORTITUDE VS. FURIOUS</span><b>, By Some monk</b><br><br>When you are being attacked from behind by a mob, it will say you riposte, but another message will come up and say &#34;you can't see your target from here.&#34;<P>
When running for the zone, use Fortitude.  You will riposte every attack (you won't counter, but they still can't hit past your riposte).  The Furious discipline lasts for 9 seconds, while this one lasts for 8.<P>
What is this good for?  Probably if the mob has a damage shield and you don't want to kill yourself riposte-ing everything in front of you.

<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>SEEMS TO ME</span><b>, By Skog</b><br><br>Looks to me, the description of furious states &#34;will riposte all attacks from opponents he is facing.&#34; So, maybe the riposte from Furious will not account for attacks from behind, like a normal riposte? I am a long way from getting any discipline, just curious. Maybe that is what is &#34;supposed&#34; to make Fortitude better is that is works on any attack.<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>JUST AN OPINION</span><b>, By Myotis</b><br><br>The only way I could see any use for this is if it sheilded magic too . Maybe they will fix it until then I'll just use the repost all disipline because its everything this one is and more . I really wish I didnt have to beg for endures and resists , this would probly do the job if they fixed it .<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>RIPOSTE</span><b>, By Ss</b><br><br>Uhmm, yes you can riposte something that is behind, it is true you won't attack back, but you still don't take damage because you &#34;&#34;riposte&#34;&#34;
<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
    <tr>
      <td width='95%' align='left' valign='top' colspan=2 class='db'><span class='dbti'>VS FURIOUS</span><b>, By Ropise</b><br><br>Riptose (sp), as everyone else has said, is opposite of rogues backstab, rogues do it from behind, Riptose is from the front. 

A  <-B   C

A and C are mobs...  B is you. you are facing <- that way.
when using Furious, you will Riptose A, but NOT C. When using this, both will miss you.

If you don't understand... stay under level 50 and be bait for us casters :) that's all you are anyways... :)

Ropise<br><hr size='1'></td>
    </tr>
